{
  "texts": [
    "The total branch length in the pipanuran tree shown in Fig. 1 (including both X. laevis subgenomes) is 2.58 substitutions per fourfold synonymous site.",
    "Centromeric and telomeric tandem repeats play a critical role in the stability of chromosome structure 65.",
    "Nonetheless, other kinds of repeats also play a role in the preservation of these important chromosome landmarks 66, 67.",
    "The new X. tropicalis v10 assembly captures sequences from centromeres and distal subtelomeres that were fragmented in the previous assemblies 25, 45.",
    "The percentage of the genome covered by transposable elements is slightly higher than previously reported 45 (36.82% vs. 34%) (Supplementary Table 7)."
  ]
}